,Recommended,214730,7752396,"Posted: 25 November, 2013",all,Sardonic,"This is a damned good game.  Damned good at being multiple games, and succeeding at it.  Turn based space combat, real time space combat, text quests, real time strategy, other games would settle on a mere one or two of these, but Space Rangers HD: A War Apart is essentially the swiss army knife of space gaming.  With its consiterable polish from the previous versions, and new content, this game is a must have.  It is a perfect entry point into the game if you've never played it before.  That said, if you've played previous versions of the game, you might consiter waiting for a slight discount.  Even still, it's a bargain at any price, and will keep you entertained for literally hundreds of hours."
