,Recommended,214730,7762863,"Posted: 26 November, 2013",all,NeoSacratif,"Unlimited freedom, sandbox and hardcore are the main features of the space simulator. Unlike typical representatives of this genre, ""Space Rangers"" - arcade simulator. If severe MMORPG ""EVE Online"" is necessary to consider the impact of each weapon on energy, the ""Space Rangers"" everything is easy - just watch the weight of the ship and, if possible, buy equipment easier and better.However, the arcade has never been synonymous with ""bad game."" On the contrary, Space Rangers became a successful for Russian Game Development. Both parts.Several years passed. Developer Studio collapsed. New OS, combined with the lack of support of the game, do SR unplayable. Is this the end? No. SNK-Games, a small modding studio, enlisting the support of publisher 1C, released a reissue of the game, ""Space Rangers HD: A War Apart"". Besides of removing technical flaws and achieving good optimization, they decided to surprise us with new content. First of all - pirates.Pirates are a new faction, a belligerent with the Coalition led by a mysterious leader. Pirates were in the original, but now they are joined together, and pose the same threat to the Coalition as Dominators. Unlike robots, in pirate space systems player can fly safety. Even if the player - the captain of the coalition forces. Become a pirate group is easy: just find any pirate base and adopt a ""special offer"". What will change? Nothing. Membership in the pirate gang has no advantages, though the hull as a present is really good (at the start of the game). But it's interesting.And. .. That's all. Yes, all new features are pirates, new text quests and new hulls. In all, this is the same Space Rangers 2. In 2013, with a good graphics and new content, but still the same. If you have never played SR/SR2, you must have. This game is worth the money. But those who have played in the second part can miss this. It'll be better to come back to the second part. The main thing is to run it on your computer. To honour of game, HD-Publishing has no problems with compability.7.0"
