,Recommended,214730,26159632,"Posted: 22 October, 2016",all,Solaire the Streetwise,"This game is an amalgam of Ur-Quan Masters, text adventure games, space sims and RTS. The main game is a space sim: you're taking control of a space ship in a semi-turn-based 2D space environment. You can fight, trade, hire companions and do various tasks like patrolling sectors or delivering valuable goods. You can also enter black holes, which changes the game to an Ur-Quan-esque arcade shooter. Sometimes the quests you get on planets or stations are text adventures or RTS missions of varying difficulty. Some are balls-bustingly hard.Space Rangers is self-conscious, funny — hope they didn't lose their jokes in translation — and most importantly, Space Rangers is thoroughly enjoyable in every facet."
