76561198108269527,Recommended,214730,9603068,"Posted: 22 March, 2014",all,quantum_jak,"Space Rangers 1 and 2 are two of my favorite pc games, perhaps my favorite space-themed game. This game is an HD reboot of Space Rangers 2 with an enhanced pirate faction. It is every bit as fun as the original Space Rangers 2, just with better graphics and a more powerful pirate faction. The game is two parts turn-based tactical space combat, one part text adventure, and one part rpg with a tacked-on rts-style sidequest that occasionally pops up for good measure. Some of the quests actually require a bit of intelligent thought to solve (or else trial and error). In addition to blowing up enemy ships, interstellar trade, drug and contraband smuggling, collecting loot, and buying better ships and equipment, there are a huge variety of frequently humorous sidequests ranging from helping to destroy the last copy of the ""Windows"" virus that wreaked havoc on computers in the 20th century, managing an interstellar resort,  to actually becoming a small alien rodent.9/10"
