76561198019597917,Recommended,214730,28888896,"Posted: 31 December, 2016",all,John Don McGee,"It's a good game so far. Just starting out I found it to be extremely difficult but after figuring out the mechanics of the game it began to become a bit easier. Mid game I realized the game got way too difficult again due to the raging factions trying to take over space. I like the equipment system as everything is randomized from merchant to merchants and they have a search system to help you find what you want. This gae has a lot of depth to it if you are able to play through it. Currently I transfered over to the pirate organization which changed things for somewhat the worse so I will have to start over again. I would like to change the organization mechanics as it is a bit confusing as to who is a pirate and who is a ranger as the ship names change and ships are labeled rangers when really they are a pirate. The trading system is fine, pretty basic but it works. The game has three other ""mini-games;"" the planetary battles battles are pretty basic where you equip robots like a mech warror load out and move the robots taking capture points. Personally theres not much to think about when playing it. There are text based games which are pretty fun but the problem is that they are pretty streamlined and if you fail you can always restart and do the same thing. The last is an arcade type game where you fly around shooting ships in a seizure like background, I never got to figuring out how to play it. So far I havn't gotten too far into the story or close to succeeding at the game. I would say that if you are to buy this game is due to the space battles in turn-based mode. It is innovating at the start but it could have been even more."
76561198064388679,Recommended,214730,27279874,"Posted: 24 November, 2016",all,ZenZone1,"TL;DRGrand little gem.Detailed reviewAlthough i did not play this Steam version much, i completed SR1 & SR2 disc version a few times. This is like Freelancer except it's 2D turn based space combat and 3D ground RTS which is optional to the completion of the game. What it does better than Freelancer is everything else except cinematic story and real-time 3D combat. Do not scoff at 2D space combat. At first i thought this would be average arcade shooter, it's much more than that.ProsShip upgrades and customizations based on playstyle or preferred weaponsRoleplay as trader, mercenary, military or pirate and switch between them based on number of actions taken in each roleAssign skill points based on preferred playstyle as you level-upNPC ships and alien races remember who you are and what you did and their disposition towards you depends on your reputation with themAlien bases have their own unique thematic musicSpace combat can be detailed turn based or auto resolved with pause at any timeMany savegame slots; mistakes can easily be rectifiedRTS component is base building, resource control, unit configuration and tactics. Not my favourite genre. Fortunately it's not essential to game progression.Competition for loot with other AI ships is both fun and funnyCommunication with NPC ships for trade or temporary alliance.Trade, fight, take various missions ranging from bounty hunting to text adventures to IQ puzzles. Text adventures and IQ puzzles are amazingly fun and doesn't stress the computer too much.Did i mentioned IQ puzzles?Cool weapons and effectsNice ship designs and animationsFaction reputation determines whether NPC ships like traders, military and pirates will help you or attack you.Dynamic economy affected by movement of trade goods and planetary conditionsRanking system based on contributions to the Space Ranger cause and personal achievements. Cool titles upon reaching higher ranks in the various factions; trader, mercenary, military and pirate. Your rank determine who you can hire as wingmen.ConsNot real-time 3D space combat so a bit lacking in urgency except in the RTS component and timed missions."
