,Recommended,214730,14169107,"Posted: 25 January, 2015",all,-[FF]- Pendleton,"Space Rangers HD puts a hand in too many cookie jars and doesn't really excel in any of them. It tries to be a Myst-like adventure series with little short, interactive, branching stories, then tries its hand at being a space sim where you fly around a little and barter, and finally it tries its hand at arcade shooting and RTS style gameplay. It has variety, being a jack of all trades, but it doesn't master any of them. On the other hand, it doesn't fail horrible, save for the reading portions where you can be screwed by RNG, especially when you're on the clock. Don't buy this game unless you're sure you want any of those, or you're a fan of the series. If you are a fan, it does exactly what you want and it runs without issue. So I won't give it any hate for that. It's possible that I'm just not too big a fan of the series, and the game isn't at fault, so I give it that benefit of the doubt."
