76561197981738822,Not Recommended,214730,31754381,Posted: 14 May,all,Handsome Squidward,"I used to play this game just over a decade ago when they updated it as ""A War Apart"" so when I saw it rereleased on STEAM as an updated version I HAD to get it! So why the thumbs down? Well after playing it for a few weeks I realized that there has only been minimal changes, some are good, others not so much..The Pros:-Awesome music, especially when entering black holes, the fast paced music really immerses you into the combat. Even when travelling between star systems, the music kept me entertained and in the space exploring mood throughout my playthrough.-A lot of new ships and Weapons to choose from and experiment with.-The new Pirate Organization with a ranking system and space stations that work just like the Coalitions Military Stations.-A living breathing galaxy, the world actually moves around you, which gives a huge feeling of immersion. I liked how I could sit around and watch other NPCS move up military ranks and live their lives without any player interaction.-Fun combat elements, turn style combat which allows you to pause and strategize which was a nice feature since it allowed some micro-managing.-Open world Freedom, I like how there are no specifics one what skills you HAVE to get up first. If you want to trade, become a trader, if you want to be a jerk and rob people (Which I personally prefered) become a Pirate! The easiest and safest route I found to be was sticking with Ranger military.Now, THE CONS:-Planetary battles, the AI is incredible lack-luster in terms of reliability. The idea of putting an RTS element to an RPG game isn't necessarily a terrible idea. What IS, however, is doing it without developing a proper AI for that specific feature. For example: When telling my troops to move forward, instead my troops may walk a bit left, do a loopy-loopy to the left and down, maybe to the right a bit, walk into the walls for a few seconds, then start heading up. A process that may have taken 6-9 seconds to fully perform, when they should have taken the initial 2 seconds to just WALK FORWARD.The same goes with attacking, they pick the weirdest targets, Instead of shooting at a target that is attacking them, not even two unit lengths away, they are aiming at another target miles away in behind my own troops. I didn't mind the battles TOO much, as of writing this review I have 24/40 planetary battles completed, so I'm not saying they are impossible but what is frustrating is most of the difficulty which comes from the battles is trying to get the terrible AI to work properly for you.-Liberating Star Systems, Most of the time I find myself buying military operations which seem to have next to no effect. They will gather maybe 5 ships of extreme garbage quality, that fly into the next system and get shot down immediately. There is no intelligence behind it. Even when looking at the Galaxy map, I'll see a system currently being liberated, so I warp in to find allies fighting the dominators. But once I show up and start fighting, ALL OF MY ALLIES start warping away from the solar system. Then when I try to liberate them myself (Late game) allies will only warp in once theres only  a few dominators left.-Relationships with other Captains, I find the relationship meter with most other captains broken. I will be flying through a star system only to be interupted by another ranger demanding money from me, I tell him no so he starts shooting. If I return fire, I am now hated by other rangers in the area. This is kind of weird, seeing as I'm the guy whos getting robbed, its like walking into a walmart, only for the greeter to say, ""Your wallet or your life!"" And if you refuse, the rest of the walmart employees will start throwing items at you while you try to leave the store.-Pirate Organization ships, They use too many missle launchers. When flying into a star system, its strange to scan over 15 different ships to see each and every one of them using 5 missle launchers. In fact the game starts lagging, which stops the immersion quite quickly when the game is now taking 3-5 seconds to load in between each turn because of exploding stray missles.-With new ships comes imbalance, The sizing of a lot of ships makes the game stagnant. By mid-end game I found most ships had around 1500+ hull. Not only transports and Liners, but most rangers and military are also flying around with 1500 even up to 2000 hull size witch shield generators and droids too, which makes a lot of the fighting extremely long and repetetive.  By the very end, most fights became more of a chore than anything else.TLDR;It's mostly just poor AI which brings this game down for me. It's not like its a BAD game, its just not amazing is all, I'd say Space Rangers 2 is ""Alright"". I think where I'm most disappointed is that it has been over a decade, and they released such minimal things on this game when instead I wish they had fixed the AI issues that they had known people were having since the original release."
