76561198027423572,Not Recommended,214730,9858682,"Posted: 18 April, 2014",all,balefirez,"I really wanted to like this game.  No, I REALLY wanted to like this game.  It reminded me of another space exploration/ combat/ merchant game I used to love to play called Escape Velocity.  This was slightly different, what with the turn based movement/ combat and a RTS-type aspect with the ground combat.  But I thought that would just add to the enjoyment.My biggest problem with this game (and the reason I uninstalled it) is that they tell you nothing about anything.  You are thrown to the wolves from day one.  They do have a minor tutorial that ""instructs"" you how to play.  It took me dying 5 times in the tutorial (THE TUTORIAL) to realize that most of the useful information is displayed as a microscopic toolbar down in the bottom left of your screen.  After I saw that, I actually managed to make it past the tutorial only to die promptly thereafter to a random pirate (this wasn't in hard mode, mind you).  Also, there are so many little markings and symbols that don't have a description.  These things should be helping you, but instead just make me ask, ""Why give me descriptors that are in no way descriptive or helpful?""  There are 2 very different combat modes (one of which they don't bother explaining at all).  All-in-all, this game was just massively frustrating.This could be an AMAZING game.  All they would have to do is help you understand how the game works.  Instead, they throw you the (incomplete) Dummies guide to brain surgery and say, ""good luck, sucker.""  I will gladly pick it up again if I learn that they have added an actual descriptive explanation of how to play the game."
