76561198017484504,Recommended,214730,18350235,"Posted: 5 October, 2015",all,terrak,"This game is like a bunch of minigames all thrown together.  The main game is a spaceship/trading game,  you upgrade your ship and fight in turn based combat.  There's a lot of freedom you can be a pirate or trader for example,  different ships have different strenghts.  There's also a bunch of ""text quest"" minigames which are completely optional but can give you good amounts of credits to upgrade your ship,  some are really good but others are a bit tedious.   There's also optional RTS missions which I don't like much but they are short and give good rewards so I'll try each once and skip it if fail once.  The game is a bit of a mixed bag but the main game is solid and oddly addicting.  Early on you have to rely a lot on other rangers and military ships to fight the dominators (evil AI) but you can eventually become very powerful and hire up to 6 NPC ships and capture enemy systems by yourself."
