76561198062450009,Recommended,214730,32233327,Posted: 6 June,all,Feo,"First, let me be frank to say that my review is for the original version that I had pleasure playing 10+ years ago, i have no idea what the devs managed to improve, or (more likely) to break in the HD version. I still got an old cd lying somewhere, but let's be honest - I doubt I'll partake in that revelry any time soon.TL;DR Like future sandbox spaceships rpg/rts/text quests? Try it!I've spend many-many hours in the world of the grim but oh-so-cute future of the XXXIV century. In the ""new"" (""old"" being Space Rangers 1) installation of that Russian-made acclaimed game series we fight robots!The Good Stuff- Large, everchanging sandbox. Dosens of star systems, hundreds (or around so) planets, different space stations- Beautiful art- You can make credits by mining- You can make credits by trading (10-20 types of trading stuff)- You can make credits by robbin' traders- You can make credits by robbin' robbers- You can make credits killing absolutely everything (military, fellow rangers, pirates, robots, genestealer aliens(?))- You can go to jail (a special text quest)!- You can make credits by doing TEXT QUESTSIt's one of the types of minigames I absolutely adored. For me it breathed in life into the already vibrant galaxy.The not so Good Stuff- I'm was not a big fan of the other minigame - planetary rts battles. The battles are pretty well done, reminded me of total annihilation knock off. The were more or less fun, but I kinda did not get why a Ranger should do this.- They basically removed another minigame. In SR1 every time you travelled between systems you had an option of investigating ""warps"" or something where you'd get attacked by pirates/aliens in a 2d top down space shooter arena. It used to be real nice - all weapon types were different, you had augmentations, etc. In SR2 the only time (AFAIK) you can do this is one of the choices to fight some end-boss. And if you choose this you'd need a lot of vim to push throug as the fight is quite challenging and it is going to your first fight.- Some jokes/easter eggs might seem dumb- I did not really like to fight robots"
